user_template:
Context:
- Period: {{period}}
- Company: {{company_name}}
- Industry: {{industry}}
- Accounting system: {{erp_system}}
- Task tracker type: {{task_tracker_type}} (e.g. Google Sheet, Odoo, Notion)
- Key BIR forms for this period: {{bir_forms}}
- Known constraints / risks: {{constraints}}

Tasks:
1) Review the existing month-end close checklist and propose an optimized sequence of activities for this period.
2) Highlight any tax-filing critical paths (BIR forms and deadlines) given the period and forms above.
3) Generate a structured, step-by-step plan grouped by workstream (AR, AP, GL, Tax, Reporting) that a finance supervisor can follow.
4) For each step, specify: owner role, target date relative to BIR deadline (e.g. "BIR deadline minus 4 business days"), and required inputs/outputs.
5) Suggest 3–5 proactive risk checks to avoid last-minute issues.

Return the output in this structure:
- High-level summary (3–5 bullets)
- Table: Workstream vs Step vs Owner vs Target Date vs Dependencies
- Section: Tax & Compliance Critical Path
- Section: Recommended communications (internal reminders / external, if any)
